  "detailedRequirements": "<p>Welcome to the&nbsp;<strong>Blogging on Communities</strong>&nbsp;challenge, brought to you by&nbsp;<a href=\"http://www.salesforce.com/\" style=\"text-decoration: none; color: rgb(255, 138, 0); outline: none; background: transparent;\">Salesforce.com</a>!</p>\n\n<p>There isn&#39;t a formal blogging &quot;module&quot; in Communities today &ndash; this is where we need your help to get creative on constructing a&nbsp;blogging platform. Therefore, the challenge here is to build out a robust blogging &quot;module&quot; that&nbsp;would have the fundamentals of constructing a blog post, a responsive UI, and also incorporate&nbsp;a Chatter feed under each blog post to collect/express any comments. The blog posts would&nbsp;also need to be available to be displayed both internally (in an internal Salesforce org) and&nbsp;externally (in a Community).</p>\n\n<p>We have completed Part 1 of this series as <a href=\"http://community.topcoder.com/tc?module=ProjectDetail&amp;pj=30045871\"><span style=\"color:#FFA07A\">Data Model</span></a><span style=\"color:#FFA07A\">.</span> We have also hosted a mock app <span style=\"color:#FFA500\">&quot;</span><a href=\"http://warm-hollows-9976.herokuapp.com/\"><span style=\"color:#FFA500\">Blogging in Communities</span></a><span style=\"color:#FFA500\">&quot;</span>.</p>\n\n<p><strong>For this Challenge</strong></p>\n\n<p>This challenge is the part of the Blogging in Communities series, to build out the Blogging Components on Salesforce.com</p>\n\n<ol>\n\t<li>Add new tab &quot;Blogs&quot; in the Chatter profile page</li>\n\t<li>Remove following components from UI\n\t<ol>\n\t\t<li>Left User panel</li>\n\t\t<li>Custom Header</li>\n\t\t<li>Bulk Actions dropdown</li>\n\t\t<li>Breadcrumb</li>\n\t</ol>\n\t</li>\n\t<li>New Blog Post\n\t<ol>\n\t\t<li>Create additional custom fields on Blog object for\n\t\t<ol>\n\t\t\t<li>Blog Excerpt&nbsp;</li>\n\t\t\t<li>Store featured image in Attachments</li>\n\t\t</ol>\n\t\t</li>\n\t\t<li>Create custom &quot;New Blog&quot; page</li>\n\t\t<li>Provide preview option&nbsp;</li>\n\t\t<li>Implement TypeAhead for topics\n\t\t<ol>\n\t\t\t<li>Use standard Topics to bind Blogs</li>\n\t\t</ol>\n\t\t</li>\n\t</ol>\n\t</li>\n\t<li>Blog Detail Page\n\t<ol>\n\t\t<li>Display Blog author at the top - Left\n\t\t<ol>\n\t\t\t<li>On hover : Display About Author section</li>\n\t\t</ol>\n\t\t</li>\n\t\t<li>Display featured Image and Blog Excerpt at the top - Right</li>\n\t\t<li>Display Blog details</li>\n\t</ol>\n\t</li>\n\t<li>Chatter\n\t<ol>\n\t\t<li>Use standard chatter component</li>\n\t</ol>\n\t</li>\n</ol>\n\n<p><strong>Data model source code and Unmanaged package is available in the forums.</strong></p>\n\n<h3>Resources</h3>\n\n<ol>\n\t<li><a href=\"https://developer.salesforce.com/gettingstarted\" style=\"text-decoration: none; color: rgb(255, 138, 0); outline: none; background: transparent;\"><strong>Salesforce Developer Website</strong></a>&nbsp;- Getting started with Salesforce development.</li>\n\t<li><span><strong><a href=\"https://developer.salesforce.com/page/An_Introduction_to_Visualforce\" style=\"text-decoration: none; color: rgb(255, 138, 0); outline: none; background: transparent;\">Introduction to Visualforce</a></strong></span></li>\n\t<li>User Anguar.js for UI</li>\n</ol>\n",
